Title: C++ VS Code GCC CMake Setup

Category: Languages and Runtimes

Description: Initial C++ development setup on Ubuntu with GCC, CMake, GDB, Ninja, and VS Code.

Intro: This page sets up a simple C++ project with GCC, CMake, GDB, Ninja, and VS Code. It is designed as a first working reference for compiling, building, debugging, and running a small C++ project from both VS Code and the terminal.

Section: Create main.cpp

Create the first source file under src. This confirms that the compiler, CMake target, and build path work end to end.

Code (bash):
nano src/main.cpp

Paste the following:

Code (bash):
#include <iostream>

int main() {
 std::cout << "Hello from C++ on Ubuntu" << std::endl;
 return 0;
}

