Title: FastAPI Setup with Docker

Category: FastAPI Project Examples

Description: A FastAPI setup project that runs fully inside Docker and exposes basic JSON routes.

Intro: This setup creates the smallest FastAPI project. The app runs inside Docker, installs Python dependencies inside the container, and exposes a basic route.

Section: Create the FastAPI app

Create the main FastAPI application file at app/main.py. This file defines the FastAPI application instance and two simple GET routes. The root route returns a basic message and the health route returns a status response.

Code (text):
app/main.py

Code (python):
from fastapi import FastAPI

app = FastAPI(title="01 Basic Route")

@app.get("/")
def home():
 return {
 "message": "Hello from FastAPI running in Docker"
 }

@app.get("/health")
def health():
 return {
 "status": "ok"
 }

